  "page_end_sec": 243.22,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.588,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.768,
      "end": 3.74,
      "text": "Chapter VIII of The Maltese Falcon by Dashiell Hammett."
    },
    {
      "start": 4.52,
      "end": 6.78,
      "text": "This LibriVox recording is in the public domain."
    },
    {
      "start": 7.92,
      "end": 8.52,
      "text": "Horse Feathers"
    },
    {
      "start": 9.09,
      "end": 12.62,
      "text": "Brigid O'Shaughnessy was huddled in the armchair by the table.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 13.08,
      "end": 15.02,
      "text": "Her forearms were up over her cheeks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 15.2,
      "end": 18.08,
      "text": "her knees drawn up until they hid the lower part of her face."
    },
    {
      "start": 19.02,
      "end": 20.72,
      "text": "Her eyes were white-circled and terrified."
    },
    {
      "start": 22.04,
      "end": 23.54,
      "text": "Joel Cairo stood in front of her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 23.64,
      "end": 24.52,
      "text": "bending over her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.152,
      "end": 28.26,
      "text": "holding in one hand the pistol Spade had twisted out of his hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 28.75,
      "end": 30.86,
      "text": "His other hand was clapped to his forehead."
    },
    {
      "start": 31.72,
      "end": 33.18,
      "text": "Blood ran through the fingers of that"
    },
    {
      "start": 33.18,
      "end": 35.28,
      "text": "hand and down under them to his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 36.16,
      "end": 37.86,
      "text": "A smaller trickle from his cut lip"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.22,
      "end": 40.28,
      "text": "made three wavy lines across his chin."
    },
    {
      "start": 41.344,
      "end": 43.34,
      "text": "Cairo did not heed the detectives.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 43.94,
      "end": 46.46,
      "text": "He was glaring at the girl huddled in front of him."
    },
    {
      "start": 46.92,
      "end": 48.68,
      "text": "His lips were working spasmodically,"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.28,
      "end": 51.5,
      "text": "but no coherent sound came from between them."
    },
    {
      "start": 52.32,
      "end": 52.7,
      "text": "Dundy,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 52.82,
      "end": 54.84,
      "text": "the first of the three into the living-room,"
    },
    {
      "start": 54.9,
      "end": 56.34,
      "text": "moved swiftly to Cairo's side,"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.62,
      "end": 59.86,
      "text": "put a hand on his own hip under his overcoat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.0,
      "end": 64.92,
      "text": "a hand on the Levantine's wrist, and growled: \"What are you up to here?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 65.82,
      "end": 67.48,
      "text": "Cairo took the red-smeared",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 67.46,
      "end": 69.9,
      "text": "hand from his head and flourished it close to the"
    },
    {
      "start": 69.96,
      "end": 73.0,
      "text": "Lieutenant's face. Uncovered by the hand, his"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.0,
      "end": 75.77,
      "text": "forehead showed a three-inch ragged tear. \"This"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.1,
      "end": 78.82,
      "text": "is what she has done,\" he cried. \"Look at it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 79.8,
      "end": 81.88,
      "text": "The girl put her feet down on the floor and looked",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 82.14,
      "end": 83.04,
      "text": "warily from Dundy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.16,
      "end": 84.5,
      "text": "holding Cairo's wrist,"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.02,
      "end": 85.72,
      "text": "to Tom Polhaus,"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.98,
      "end": 87.62,
      "text": "standing a little behind them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 87.74,
      "end": 88.66,
      "text": "to Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.86,
      "end": 90.68,
      "text": "leaning against the door-frame."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.68,
      "end": 93.38,
      "text": "Spade's face was placid."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.69,
      "end": 95.08,
      "text": "When his gaze met hers,"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.2,
      "end": 97.36,
      "text": "his yellow-grey eyes glinted for an instant with"
    },
    {
      "start": 97.36,
      "end": 99.92,
      "text": "malicious humor and then became expressionless"
    },
    {
      "start": 100.12,
      "end": 100.3,
      "text": "again."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.78,
      "end": 102.12,
      "text": "\"Did you do that?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 102.34,
      "end": 103.6,
      "text": "Dundy asked the girl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.7,
      "end": 105.04,
      "text": "nodding at Cairo's cut head."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.02,
      "end": 106.74,
      "text": "She looked at Spade",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 106.84,
      "end": 107.04,
      "text": "again."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.25,
      "end": 110.46,
      "text": "He did not in any way respond to the appeal in her eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.66,
      "end": 112.94,
      "text": "He leaned against the door-frame and"
    },
    {
      "start": 113.04,
      "end": 114.92,
      "text": "observed the occupants of the room with the"
    },
    {
      "start": 114.92,
      "end": 117.92,
      "text": "polite detached air of a disinterested spectator."
    },
    {
      "start": 118.38,
      "end": 120.76,
      "text": "The girl turned her eyes up to Dundy's.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 120.88,
      "end": 123.08,
      "text": "Her eyes were wide and dark and earnest."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.94,
      "end": 124.46,
      "text": "\"I had to,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 124.54,
      "end": 126.16,
      "text": "she said in a low throbbing voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 126.44,
      "end": 129.14,
      "text": "\"I was all alone in here with him when he attacked me."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.32,
      "end": 130.44,
      "text": "I couldn't—"
    },
    {
      "start": 130.62,
      "end": 132.06,
      "text": "I tried to keep him off."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.992,
      "end": 135.18,
      "text": "I—I couldn't make myself shoot him.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 136.24,
      "end": 136.4,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 136.5,
      "end": 137.14,
      "text": "you liar!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 137.46,
      "end": 138.12,
      "text": "Cairo cried,"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.78,
      "end": 140.68,
      "text": "trying unsuccessfully to pull the arm"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.68,
      "end": 142.76,
      "text": "that held his pistol out of Dundy's grip."
    },
    {
      "start": 143.58,
      "end": 143.94,
      "text": "\"Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 143.94,
      "end": 144.52,
      "text": "you dirty,"
    },
    {
      "start": 144.54,
      "end": 145.24,
      "text": "filthy liar!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 146.28,
      "end": 148.24,
      "text": "He twisted himself around to face Dundy."
    },
    {
      "start": 148.86,
      "end": 149.64,
      "text": "\"She's lying awfully."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.48,
      "end": 153.28,
      "text": "I came here in good faith and was attacked by both of them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 153.7,
      "end": 154.36,
      "text": "and when you came"
    },
    {
      "start": 154.88,
      "end": 156.16,
      "text": "he went out to talk to you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.544,
      "end": 157.96,
      "text": "leaving her here with this pistol,"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.44,
      "end": 160.36,
      "text": "and then she said they were going to kill me"
    },
    {
      "start": 160.32,
      "end": 162.36,
      "text": "after you left, and I called for help,"
    },
    {
      "start": 162.36,
      "end": 164.6,
      "text": "so you wouldn't leave me here to be murdered,"
    },
    {
      "start": 164.84,
      "end": 166.96,
      "text": "and then she struck me with the pistol.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 167.84,
      "end": 168.7,
      "text": "\"Here, give me this",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 168.8,
      "end": 171.62,
      "text": "thing,\" Dundy said, and took the pistol from Cairo's hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.32,
      "end": 174.18,
      "text": "\"Now let's get this straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.18,
      "end": 174.88,
      "text": "What'd you come here for?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 175.28,
      "end": 176.92,
      "text": "\"He sent for me.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 177.08,
      "end": 180.18,
      "text": "Cairo twisted his head around to stare defiantly at Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 180.7,
      "end": 183.06,
      "text": "\"He called me up on the phone and asked me to come here.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 183.936,
      "end": 186.28,
      "text": "Spade blinked sleepily at the Levantine and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 186.4,
      "end": 186.76,
      "text": "said nothing."
    },
    {
      "start": 188.0,
      "end": 188.5,
      "text": "Dundy asked:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 188.66,
      "end": 189.96,
      "text": "\"What'd he want you for?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 191.04,
      "end": 193.16,
      "text": "Cairo withheld his reply until he had mopped",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 193.16,
      "end": 195.12,
      "text": "his bloody forehead and chin with a"
    },
    {
      "start": 195.12,
      "end": 196.66,
      "text": "lavender-barred silk handkerchief."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.08,
      "end": 198.16,
      "text": "By then some of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 198.24,
      "end": 200.58,
      "text": "indignation in his manner had been replaced by caution."
    },
    {
      "start": 201.18,
      "end": 202.32,
      "text": "\"He said he wanted—"
    },
    {
      "start": 202.48,
      "end": 203.58,
      "text": "they wanted—"
    },
    {
      "start": 203.76,
      "end": 204.6,
      "text": "to see me."
    },
    {
      "start": 205.14,
      "end": 206.4,
      "text": "I didn't know what about.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 207.424,
      "end": 209.02,
      "text": "Tom Polhaus lowered his head,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 209.2,
      "end": 211.64,
      "text": "sniffed the odor of _chypre_ that the"
    },
    {
      "start": 211.78,
      "end": 214.1,
      "text": "mopping handkerchief had released in the air, and"
    },
    {
      "start": 214.112,
      "end": 217.28,
      "text": "turned his head to scowl interrogatively at Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 218.304,
      "end": 220.62,
      "text": "Spade winked at him and went on rolling a cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 221.728,
      "end": 222.32,
      "text": "Dundy asked:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 222.56,
      "end": 222.66,
      "text": "\"Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.62,
      "end": 224.34,
      "text": "what happened then?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 225.42,
      "end": 226.48,
      "text": "\"Then they attacked me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 227.0,
      "end": 229.2,
      "text": "She struck me first, and then he choked"
    },
    {
      "start": 229.2,
      "end": 230.9,
      "text": "me and took the pistol out of my"
    },
    {
      "start": 231.02,
      "end": 231.34,
      "text": "pocket."
    },
    {
      "start": 232.3,
      "end": 233.62,
      "text": "I don't know what they would have done"
    },
    {
      "start": 233.62,
      "end": 235.56,
      "text": "next if you hadn't arrived at that moment."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.36,
      "end": 238.74,
      "text": "I dare say they would have murdered me then and there."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.66,
      "end": 241.28,
      "text": "When he went out to answer the bell he left"
    },
    {
      "start": 241.28,
      "end": 243.18,
      "text": "her here with the pistol to watch over me.\""
    }
  ]
}